@node inventscorner "Invent's Corner"
@toc contents
============================================================================
 	 @{b}Invent's Corner@{ub} - by: @{"Kevin Saunders" link kevinsaunders}
============================================================================

  As the end of the year approaches, it's time to reflect on 2022 and start 
  thinking about priorities for 2023, Amiga, Classic, NG and Other.

  For classic Amiga's the game @{b}Reshoot Proxima III@{ub} is getting ever closer 
  to release. Richard, Martin and myself are extremely proud of our third 
  and final in the series (well at least it's my last in the series). 
  Richard and I have worked closely over the years on these games and I am 
  honoured to be working with him and our great team. If you haven't 
  visited AmigaBill's Twitch please do as Bill certainly please our demo 
  really well. Don't forget to visit Richard's preview youtube demo here: 
  
  https://youtu.be/_fLdudinjHY

  @{b}Aquabyss@{ub} is finally released, I really enjoyed working with Peter on his 
  Amiga project, and while I have various posts on the development process 
  on my blog, the best place to visit the project is on Peter's website 
  here: 
  
  https://agedcode.com/agedcode/en/

  What's happened to @{b}Boss Machine@{ub}, not much but it's always on my mind. Dan 
  who is a great friend and local coder in Brisbane certainly deserves more 
  of my time on this project, he is also one of my generous Patreons and 
  deserves more of my time and attention. 2023 will be given a lot more 
  attention for this very exciting project. For all the behind the scenes 
  please visit here: 
  
  https://www.patreon.com/KevinSaunders?filters[tag]=BOSS%20Machine

  The last few months have been focused on @{b}Apollo Invaders@{ub} for anyone who 
  has a V2 or V4 Vampire card. Gunnar, Arne, Martin and myself have been 
  enhancing the game. My recent involvement was adding 100 custom locations 
  from famous locations around the world where you play (destroy) the 
  aliens in. Last week I was finalizing the win victory section. The time 
  now must be spent testing and tweaking any elements we need to improve. 
  More info is usually posted in our Apollogames channel on Discord: 
  
  https://discord.gg/Um5KZ5uqDk

  After @{b}Apollo Invaders@{ub}, I plan on creating a shoot em up for the Amiga 
  Vampire machines called @{b}Apollo X@{ub}, besides having two player options we
  plan on a few more exciting features, definitely, one game to follow and 
  the best place is, of course, my blog or Apollo discord. I do also have a 
  placeholder on Facebook. 
  
  https://www.facebook.com/groups/419549690142105

